properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A low pressure system currently developing over Alberta will track northeastward toward southern Kivalliq over the next couple days. Rain and easterly winds gusting up to 70 km/h will move into Arviat, Rankin Inlet and Chesterfield Inlet beginning Sunday afternoon. Overnight on Sunday, winds will increase with gusts up to 80 km/h forecast, with Rankin and Chesterfield Inlet possibly seeing wind gusts in excess of 90 km/h by Monday morning. These strong winds will gradually diminish Monday evening. The rain will persist through to Tuesday. For Baker Lake, the precipitation will move into the community as wet snow beginning Sunday evening, with gusty easterly winds strengthening overnight. Surface temperatures will be mild, but snow may be coming down heavy at times, so it is likely to accumulate on the ground. Heaviest accumulations are expected on Monday with up to 10 cm possible by Monday evening. Along with the snow, on Monday, winds will increase with gusts up to 80 km/h. The precipitation will transition to rain by Tuesday morning and winds will gradually diminish. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.
Expires: 2020-10-11T11:39:50-00:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Environment Canada, 2020-10-10T19:40:50-00:00, urn:oid:2.49.0.1.124.3813816472.2020
Area: Baker Lake, Arviat, Rankin Region including Whale Cove, Chesterfield Inlet
